<br>
It also might clarify some things about what exactly immortality is. Everywhere that we look in the universe, things are winding down, accumulating entropy so to speak. To discover that our universe could support truly immortal beings would force us to completely rethink many aspects of reality. If immortal beings can live among us, then some aspect of existence itself must also be immortal. Otherwise when space and time end so will immortal beings, which kind of defeats the point.<br>
<br>
To become truly immortal, beyond simply living young a long time and then dying, would necessitate becoming something other than human. It would require giving up nearly all frailty, both physical and mental. How much change would be required, and how much humanity would be lost in such a transition?<br>
